@NODE Introduction "ShowComment 1.03"
@{B}Introduction@{UB}

 ShowComment.rexx is an ARexx program that searches for and displays any text
 comments contained in a JPEG or GIF file.

 NOTE: ShowComment.rexx will only search for comments in JFIF JPEG files, as
 this is the only type of JPEG file that it was designed to recognize.  This
 limitation is due to the fact that I have no information on the other
 varieties (HSI JPEGs, TIFF JPEGs, PICT JPEGs, & others?) of JPEGs.  I don't
 even know if they can contain comments.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Requirements "ShowComment 1.03"
@{B}Requirements@{UB}

 ARexx
@ENDNODE




@NODE Installation "ShowComment 1.03"
@{B}Installation@{UB}

 Copy ShowComment.rexx to your S: directory or elsewhere.
@ENDNODE




@NODE UsingIt "ShowComment 1.03"
@{B}Using It@{UB}

 ShowComment.rexx should be run from the Shell/CLI.  Its usage is as follows:

     RX ShowComment.rexx <filename>

 or if its "s" protection bit is set:

     ShowComment.rexx <filename>

 where <filename> is the complete path and filename of a JPEG or GIF file.

 Once it starts, ShowComment.rexx will display:

     @{B}ShowComment 1.03 - Copyright (c) 1995 by Felix C. Coronado@{UB}

 If the file you pick is a JPEG or GIF file, ShowComment.rexx will then
 display the following:

     Searching for comments in '<filename>'...
     Ctrl-d to stop

 ShowComment.rexx is now searching the selected file for comments.  If you
 press Ctrl-d (the "Ctrl" key and the "d" key at the same time) while "Ctrl-d
 to stop" is displayed, ShowComment.rexx will stop searching for comments.
 Pressing Ctrl-c while "Ctrl-d to stop" is displayed will abort the program.

 If you stop the search before any comments are found, or if no comments are
 found, ShowComment.rexx will display the words "No Comment".

 If ShowComment.rexx is able to find comments, it will display the following:

     @{B}Comment@{UB} <number>@{B}:@{UB} <Comment>
@ENDNODE




@NODE Author "ShowComment 1.03"
@{B}Contacting the Author@{UB}

 If you have any bug reports, questions, suggestions, comments, or gifts to
 send me or if you would like information about the most recent versions of
 my programs, I would be glad to hear from you.  I would particularly like to
 hear from you if:

 1. You come across a JPEG or GIF file that you know contains comments but
   ShowComment.rexx does not recognize it or does not display the comments.
   If this occurs, I would appreciate it if you sent me a copy of the file so
   that I could try to fix the problem.

 2. You have any information relating to:
    a. JPEG and GIF file comments (programs that let you add/edit them, etc.)
    b. the various JPEG file formats (the structure of JPEG files, what JPEG
      file formats contain comments, etc.)

 I can be reached at:

 E-mail:
        Internet: (if you don't get a reply from one address, try the other)
                  felixthecat@geocities.com
                  75460.722@compuserve.com

      CompuServe: 75460,722

 WWW: www.geocities.com/Paris/2866
@ENDNODE




@NODE History "ShowComment 1.03"
@{B}History@{UB}

 1.03 May 21, 1995 - Minor improvements
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.02 April 5, 1995 - ShowComment.rexx can now detect GIF file comments
                      shorter than 255 characters
                    - ShowComment.rexx now displays only the actual comment
                      text in GIF files
                    - Multiple GIF file comments are now displayed separately
                    - ShowComment.rexx no longer differentiates between JPEG
                      "Creation info" comments and other JPEG file comments
                    - Other minor improvements
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.01 April 2, 1995 - Minor improvements
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.00 March 26, 1995 - Changed name from ReadJPEG.rexx to ShowComment.rexx
                     - Added support for GIF file comments
                     - Files are now read in variable size blocks (default
                       64K)
                     - When using with JPEG files, ShowComment.rexx now
                       searches the entire file for comments, instead of
                       stopping at a certain point
                     - Other minor improvements
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.03 March 10, 1995 - ReadJPEG.rexx should now be able to recognize all
                       JFIF JPEG files
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.02 March 6, 1995 - ReadJPEG.rexx now detects multiple "Comment" comments
                      if they are present and displays them as
                      "Comment <number>"
                    - Other minor improvements
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.01 March 1, 1995 - Fixed a bug that could prevent ReadJPEG.rexx from
                      detecting "Comment:" comments in certain rare cases
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.0 February 23, 1995 - First public release
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE




@NODE OtherStuff "ShowComment 1.02"
@{B}Other Stuff by Felix Coronado@{UB}

 Look for these other fine ARexx scripts/programs by Felix Coronado:

 Cataloger - ARexx script for The Art Department Professional v2.x or
             MorphPlus.  Makes image catalogs containing thumbnails of
             selected files.
             Features include:
             - Loads & saves most ADPro/MorphPlus file formats
             - Many options, different combinations can be saved & loaded
             - Files can be picked from requesters, FRED Sequence files, or
               ASCII file lists

 GIF_+_Comment - ARexx script that acts as a pseudo-Loader for The Art
                 Department Professional v2.5.  Loads a GIF file while
                 displaying any text comments contained in the file.

 JPEG_+_Comment - ARexx script that acts as a pseudo-Loader for The Art
                  Department Professional v2.5.  Loads a JPEG file while
                  displaying any text comments contained in the file.
@ENDNODE




